{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "67a2ee98c8b73881fdaea13f", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9a"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "67a2eb5ca6d4514bf2d9760a", "title": "JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "A point particle of charge $Q$ is located at $P$ along the axis of an electric dipole 1 at a distance $r$ as shown in the figure. The point P is also on the equatorial plane of a second electric dipole 2 at a distance r . The dipoles are made of opposite charge q separated by a distance $2 a$. For the charge particle at P not to experience any net force, which of the following correctly describes the situation?\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/9ILYTFGggRyAWT3KDngOt6OpW4_gDv69p2UnTR5dPd8.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "M7MaF", "text": "$\\frac{a}{r} \\sim 10$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "9VUeE", "text": "$\\frac{a}{r} \\sim 20$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "nIcEC", "text": "$\\frac{a}{r} \\sim 0.5$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "gj6sQ", "text": "$\\frac{a}{r} \\sim 3$", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<img src=\"https://cdn.quizrr.in/question-assets/jee_main_pyq/wY7ZXuyVByQ1VIYJvXdGNehoj4tnum1VnMqhXRunpYw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\r\n$\\begin{aligned}\r\n& \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{(r-a)^2}-\\frac{1}{(r+a)^2}=\\frac{2 a}{\\left(a^2+r^2\\right)^{3 / 2}} \\\\\r\n& \\frac{4 a r}{\\left(r^2-a^2\\right)^2}=\\frac{2 a}{\\left(a^2+r^2\\right)^{3 / 2}} \\\\\r\n& \\left(r^2-a^2\\right)^2=2 r\\left(a^2+r^2\\right)^{3 / 2} \\\\\r\n& \\left(1-\\frac{a^2}{r^2}\\right)^2=2\\left(1+\\frac{a^2}{r^2}\\right)^{3 / 2} \\\\\r\n& \\left(1-x^2\\right)^2=2\\left(1+x^2\\right)^{3 / 2}\\left(x=\\frac{a}{r}\\right) \\\\\r\n& \\frac{\\left(1-x^2\\right)^2}{\\left(1+x^2\\right)^{3 / 2}}=2\r\n\\end{aligned}$\r\n\r\nNow for $\\mathrm{X}=3$\r\nWe get $\\frac{64}{10 \\sqrt{10}} \\approx 2 \\Rightarrow \\frac{a}{r} \\approx 3$\r\n[But for $a > r$ point charge will between the dipole where $\\vec{E} \\neq 0$]", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ250123010026", "priority": "Priority A", "isRemoved": false, "updatedAt": "2025-03-13T09:00:28.982Z", "updated_by": "65d0c176a8f74604505ba6f6", "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616024041a305c0e66419287", "61602405c04b6efc2d30aed2", "61964c87b2e3ece4a3ae08f5", "61c089968f11857e2cc22ac4", "61964c88aedbe61edbf4a8ad", "6160240548aa12a5f67c1a13", "61bb8218a1451a3af02543bc", "61e7bd7581a69b0b3a599b78", "61602402632932165bf0ef64", "61602407c6302cf0196ff8b1", "629109ecd51d11c3d30d1b00", "629621228b45dfe178855e12", "629f390b647d372f60ea38d1", "629f3a90c1d078c63b9fb649", "64eb06c23118f713ecfef091", "66d58538a75f05ee8564f554", "67921d6a1d5b5072da5e9ada", "67fdff48378e1624ea7b699b", "6809202d3a10446a207fdefc"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}